<br>
Yes, when i signed up as a warrior, I signed up to be the best tank, to have the best AC/HP, to be the most mana efficient.   Somewhere in the last few months, that edge is *gone*, and the difference in tankability has been minimized, and manacosts of keeping alternate tanks has also become minimized. <br>
<br>
When I signed up for the game, it was FAR cheaper to cast a small heal on an ancillary party member than it was to completely heal the tank, now it's the same (*&amp;(*&amp; thing.     <br>
<br>
I also had some other exclusive things in relation to knights.<br>
<br>
1. Critical hits <br>
2. Crippling blows <br>
3. An extra attack per melee round <br>
4. Access to the best armors <br>
5. Access to the best weapons <br>
6. A margin of defensive skill over all others <br>
7. A different damage table than knights<br>
<br>
Yes, ALL melee things.. gone.. poof... not exactly what I signed up for now is it?   So pardon me if I say &quot;gee friggin whiz, if we're going to be caught up to in such a degree on our MELEE skills, it sure would be nice to be able to generate a little aggro at the outset of a fight&quot;.   <br>
