<br>
Wednesday night we had the night off from raiding, so I hooked up with some old friends in BoT and was tanking for them.<br>
<br>
We had a shadowknight join us a little later in the night and he decided that a 63 SK was better able to tank than me. He didn't say as much but he was using all his high aggro tricks. I told the monk (who is one of the great guys in EQ and my old Guild Leader) to watch this.<br>
<br>
I pulled out my Plankton Laced Greatsword, which is like zero aggro since it hits like once a week, and let the SK take and have aggro.<br>
<br>
After three rezs in three mobs he decided that aggro was better left to me.<br>
<br>
I was laughing so hard I almost fell out of my chair.<br>
<br>
